PLANTS OF SOUTH CAROLINA, U.S.A.

*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt
Diapensiaceae

Greenville Co.

Common in periphery of south facing cataract fen forest in cation rich main cataract fen seepage stream directly above Oil Camp Creek, located in Mountain Bridge Wilderness Area, east of Caesars Head State Park headquarters. USGS Cleveland 7.5' quad. Associated with *Liriodendron tulipifera*, *Rhododendron arborescens*, *Vaccinium arboreum*, *Parnassia grandifolia*, *Trautvetteria caroliniensis* var. *caroliniensis*, *Carex deflexa*, *Oxypolis rigidior*, etc.

David T. Nestor 51                      22 May 2000
